# Web App Testing (Tailscale)

When the user asks to start/launch the webapp for testing:

## 1. Build the Flutter web app in release mode

```bash
cd apps/mobile
flutter build web --release
```

Debug mode (`flutter run`) does NOT work for remote access — WebSocket debug connections fail from other devices.

## 2. Kill any previous server on port 8080

```bash
lsof -ti:8080 | xargs kill -9 2>/dev/null
```

## 3. Serve the build with Python HTTP server

```bash
cd apps/mobile/build/web
python3 -m http.server 8080 --bind 0.0.0.0
```

## 4. Give the user the Tailscale URL

```
http://100.74.29.56:8080
```

- Tailscale IP: `100.74.29.56`
- Port: `8080`
- The user accesses this URL from their iPhone via Tailscale VPN

## Notes

- If code changes are made, rebuild (`flutter build web --release`) and refresh the browser
- No hot reload available in release mode — must rebuild each time
- `--web-renderer html` flag no longer exists in current Flutter — just use `--release`
